Text: One uneventful day...

Oh yeah, Alpha, did you live in an elven forest
before?
Cid asks me this playfully.
Yes, I did. Elves love nature, you know.

They mostly live in villages they build deep in the
forests.
Hmm...
Cid places one hand on his chin as if in thought.
Are there forests like that around here?
What? Yes, there's one I know about, but...

Elves are generally averse to interacting with
outsiders, even other elves.
I see... They should watch out for fires.
Fires?

If Cid has gone out of his way to mention fire,
he must know something!
...Alright. I'll go warn them to be careful.

I nod at Cid's words and leave instantly. I head
straight for the one elven forest I know of nearby.

Well, it's a pretty standard trope for elven forests
to get burned down in light novels and manga.
I just hope nothing's happened...

Although the forest is nearby, the elves reside deep
within. By the time I reach their village, the sun has
completely set.

Cid's words always possess a hidden, deeper meaning.
This time won't be any different!

Deep in the darkness where dense foliage hides the
moonlight, a bright light glows eerily out of place.
There—fire!

Nothing beats fire when it comes to hunting elves.
You boys ready?

Damn right. Let's smoke 'em out and bag every
one of 'em.

Pretty little things, those elves—they'll make for
easy money.
Bastards...!

Seeing them attempting to set fire to the forest,
I instantly perceive their intentions and my blood
boils with rage.

Don't let 'em get singed. They're our precious goods,
you know. If you're gonna hurt 'em, make sure it's in
a place you can't see!

Yeah, yeah, we know the drill! Let's get started
then—
Hyaah!

As the slaver extends a burning torch to set a large
tree on fire, I slash off his arm without a moment's
hesitation.
Huh?

Only when the slaver sees his severed arm on the
ground, still clutching the torch, does he realize
it's his.

Ughh...aaggghhh! Th-The hell do you think you're
doing?!

Should've asked yourself that! What do you think
you're doing to this forest?!
Damn it, they've caught on! How'd you find us?!

Hold on. It's just the one brat. Looks like we've
caught us our first slave of the night, boys.
Amongst the panicking slavers, only one remains calm.

That's right, he's the boss, just like when I was
taken away as a slave...
Nooo! Stop!!! Help me!!!

What the...? That's one filthy elf. We really supposed
to be taking this one?

That's right. She's one of the possessed. Worthless
as a slave, but she'll fetch us a handsome price to
transport.
The hell? Why can't we get someone else to do it?

You haven't been in this business long, have you?
Transporting these mounds of flesh comes with
the job.
Ughh...

True, only a slaver would be willing to transport
something like this.

Just by transporting these pathetic, god-forsaken
wretches, we'll make a killing off the Church.
I'll never...ever...forgive...agghh! Ahh...aaaahhh!!!

You're a blight on this world! I'll take out every
last one of you!
H-Huhh...! Who the hell—?

I cut him down with a single stroke. Before he can
finish screaming, I pierce his throat with my blade.

I couldn't scream in the end as well. I'll make all
of you suffer the same agony I suffered!
A-Ahh...h-help...

It finally dawns on the slaver boss that they are
massively outpowered, and he collapses to the
ground.

I'm itching to cut him into pieces with my blade,
and yet...
Taking out these men won't change anything.

I lower my sword and suppress the flames of revenge
burning in my heart.

Calm down... Think of what Shadow would do in this
situation...

Give in to your emotions and you're no better than a
beast. If you want to follow in his footsteps—think.

The slavers have uncovered the location of the elves
deep within the forest.

They should have gotten lost before making it this
far, so the intel is definitely doing the rounds.

Even if I annihilate them here, a second or third
group will just replace them down the line. In that
case...

Lay your hands on this forest again, and I'll be
waiting for you.

I lift my sword ever so slightly and hold it to the
boss's throat. The blade tip presses threateningly
against his skin.

I am the shadows, and shadows exist everywhere. Don't
think you can escape me.

I draw back my sword. The tip comes away painted a
light crimson.
E-Eeeeek! I-I'll never come back here! I promise!!!

The boss leaps into a nearby bush and scrambles away
into the distance.
*sigh*

I extinguish the torch still lying on the ground.
Peaceful darkness descends on the forest.

I tried to imitate Shadow... I wonder how effective
it was.

I feel like a dull blade next to him, unable to come
near the overwhelming presence of his razor-sharp
sword.

But a dull blade is still a blade—effective enough to
at least scare off a pack of slavers.
I'll need to devote myself further.
I'm home.
Welcome back. Where'd you go?

Cid betrays no signs of the knowledge I know
he possesses. Yet hidden behind his leisurely
demeanor, his gaze sees everything.
I just stepped out for a bit.

Not to be outdone by his casual yet confident
manner, I straighten my back and speak more
assertively than I feel.
You really are amazing.

In response to my praise, Shadow doesn't budge an
inch.

Did I do something? Not sure what she's on about.
Guess I should thank her anyway.
Thanks.
This is the one I serve.

Will I ever be like him? That remains to be seen...
And yet a thought crosses my mind.

Cid...Shadow is my heart's fortress—my own deep, dark
elven forest.
